<ul class="panelbar">
    <li class="k-state-active">
        <span class="k-link k-state-selected">Question @Model?.Id</span>
        <div>
            <p>
                @Html.Raw(Model.H1OpenTag)
                Your media production company recently moved all its infrastructure into Azure.
                @Html.Raw(Model.H1CloseTag)
            </p>
            <p>
                @Html.Raw(Model.H2OpenTag)
                Every 14 days you run a batch to render several thousand video clips into various media formats for customers. At the moment the batch job is run on a single H-series virtual machine (VM). 
                @Html.Raw(Model.H2CloseTag)
            </p>
            <p>
                You need to design a scalable compute solution. The solution must meet the following technical and business requirements:
            </p>
            <p>
                Which cmdlet should you use?
            </p>
        </div>
    </li>
    <li class="k-state-active">
        Answers
        <div>
            <p>
                <ul class="fieldlist">
                    <li class="correct">
                        <input type="radio" name="group" id="@(Html.GetNextId())" class="k-radio">
                        <label class="k-radio-label" for="@(Html.GetNextId(true))">
                            Set-AzureRmVM
                        </label>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <input type="radio" name="group" id="@(Html.GetNextId())" class="k-radio">
                        <label class="k-radio-label" for="@(Html.GetNextId(true))">
                            New-AzureRmVMConfig
                        </label>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <input type="radio" name="group" id="@(Html.GetNextId())" class="k-radio">
                        <label class="k-radio-label" for="@(Html.GetNextId(true))">
                            Remove-AzureRmVM
                        </label>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <input type="radio" name="group" id="@(Html.GetNextId())" class="k-radio">
                        <label class="k-radio-label" for="@(Html.GetNextId(true))">
                            Restart-AzureRmVM
                        </label>
                    </li>
                    <li>
                        <input type="radio" name="group" id="@(Html.GetNextId())" class="k-radio">
                        <label class="k-radio-label" for="@(Html.GetNextId(true))">
                            Update-AzureRmVM
                        </label>
                    </li>
                </ul>
            </p>
        </div>
    </li>
    <li>
        Explanation
        <div>
            <p>
                You should use the Set-AzureRmVM cmdlet with the -Redeploy switch. You need to provide the resource group name and the VM name that you want to redeploy.
            </p>
            <p>
                You should not use the Update-AzureRmVM cmdlet. You use this cmdlet for updating the state of a VM to the values stored in a VM object that you can usually get using the Get-Azure RmVM cmdlet.
            </p>
            <p>
                You should not use the Restart-AzureRmVM cmdlet. This cmdlet will restart the VM. Restarting a VM does not redeploy it to a new host.
            </p>
            <p>
                You should not use the New-AzureRmVMConfig cmdlet. This cmdlet is intended for a creating new VM object configuration that you can use with other cmdlets.
            </p>
            <p>
                You should not use the Remove-AzureRmVM cmdlet. You typically use this cmdlet when you want to remove a VM from Azure.
            </p>
        </div>
    </li>
    <li>
        References
        <div>
            <p>
                <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/module/azurerm.compute/set-azurermvm" target="_blank" rel="noopener" tabindex="190">Set-AzureRmVM</a>
            </p>
            <p>
                <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/module/azurerm.compute/restart-azurermvm" target="_blank" rel="noopener" tabindex="190">Restart-AzureRmVM</a>
            </p>
            <p>
                <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/module/azurerm.compute/remove-azurermvm" target="_blank" rel="noopener" tabindex="190">Remove-AzureRmVM</a>
            </p>
            <p>
                <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/module/azurerm.compute/update-azurermvm" target="_blank" rel="noopener" tabindex="190">Update-AzureRmVM</a>
            </p>
            <p>
                <a href="https://docs.microsoft.com/en-us/powershell/module/azurerm.compute/new-azurermvmconfig" target="_blank" rel="noopener" tabindex="190">New-AzureRmVMConfig</a>
            </p>
        </div>
    </li>
</ul>